dct_title_s: British India : northern part. ; Cabul ; Nepaul.
dct_description_sm: Cartographic Details: Scales differ. Imprint derived from the atlas in which this state of the map was issued. Previous state issued in the 1817 edition of"A New General Atlas"; engraver's name removed."Drawn & engraved for Thomson's New General Atlas." Numbered"43." Shows boundaries, rivers, deserts and principal settlements; colouring shows possession. Relief shown by hachures and shading. Greenwich meridian.
16 x 15 to 35 x 60 centimeters on sheet 51 x 60 centimeters
Ames Library of South Asia Maps
